Put the @water{200%ml} in a large #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. Meanwhile, put the @Cajun spice mix{½} per serving, @honey{15%ml} and a glug of @oil{glug} in a #mixing bowl{}. Tip: The cajun spice is quite hot so only use a little if you don't like spice! Add the @British pork loin steaks{2} and mix around with your hands. Be sure to wash them afterwards!

Add the @chicken stock powder{½} to your saucepan of boiling water and give it a stir. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{100%g}, bring back to the boil, pop a lid on the #pan{} and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and finely chopped) into 1⁄2cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the pork (leave the leftover marinade in the #bowl{} for later). Cook until browned, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side. Transfer the pork to a #baking tray{} and cover with #foil{}. Roast on the top shelf of your #oven{} for ~{7-10%minutes}. Once cooked, take the pork out of your oven and leave to rest, still covered with the foil. Tip: The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

In the meantime, put your frying pan (no need to wash!) back on medium heat and add the remaining marinade and the shallot. Cook until the shallot has softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @tomato passata{1}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, some @black pepper{to taste} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some). Simmer until thick, ~{4-5%minutes}. Take off the heat.

Heat a glug of @oil{glug} in another frying pan on medium heat and add the @spring greens{150%g}(sliced) along with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and some @black pepper{to taste}. Cook until wilted, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add in the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) and cook for another ~{1%minute}.

When everything is ready, fluff up the bulgur wheat with a #fork{} and serve in #bowls{}. Slice the pork into roughly 2cm slices and serve on top with the spring greens on the side. Drizzle over some of the tomato sauce and any juices left in the baking tray. Tuck in!